subject: SYMANTEC Mail Security nonsense
msgSnippet: Someone in this group is using SYMANTEC Mail Security and it is firing a prohibited content message on /every/ e-mail I send to the group. The individual
messageBody:
Someone in this group is using SYMANTEC Mail Security and it is firing a
"prohibited content" message on /every/ e-mail I send to the group. The
individual appears to be <mholly@...>. Would this individual
please deal with this problem? I will be forced to remove the individual
from the list if these messages do not stop. At a minimum, tell me what
"prohibited content" could possibly be in my messages.

Thanks.
